<shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrc="shortdesc:1;5:13" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/schemeref.dita">A <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:2;5:27" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/schemeref.dita">schemeref</xmlelement> element references another subject
    scheme map. Typically, the referenced subject scheme defines a base set of controlled values;
    the referencing map then extends the base set of controlled values. The values specified in the
    subject scheme maps are merged; the result is equivalent to specifying all of the values in a
    single map.</shortdesc>
